1.3 Railway Bot (bot.py)

The Railway service runs two things simultaneously in one Python process:

Flask web server on PORT 8080 — handles HTTP API endpoints
Telegram scheduler — sends daily deal alerts via schedule library in a background thread

Current API endpoints:

Endpoint
Method
Purpose

/health
GET
Health check — returns {"status":"ok"}

/subscribe
POST
Adds email to Brevo list #2 using BREVO_API_KEY env var

Environment Variables (Railway)

BREVO_API_KEY — Brevo v3 API key (never commit to code)
PORT — set automatically by Railway (8080)
All secrets stored in Railway Variables dashboard only.

1.4 Supabase Schema

Five tables with Row Level Security enabled. Users can only access their own data.

Table
Key Columns

profiles
id (uuid, FK auth.users), username (unique), email, created_at

progress
id, xp, level, streak, last_daily, savings, claimed, updated_at

offer_status
user_id, offer_id, status (none/pending/completed), steps (jsonb), saved_amount

pending_payouts
user_id, offer_id, offer_name, reward, amount, due_at

badges
user_id, badge_id, earned_at

Trigger
handle_new_user() fires on auth.users INSERT — auto-creates profile and progress rows. This means signup always results in data rows existing, simplifying all subsequent queries.

