2. Known Issues & Technical Debt

Every agent must be aware of these issues before touching the codebase.

2.1 Critical Issues

CRIT-01: Single 3,700-line HTML File
app.html contains all CSS, HTML, JS, and data in one file. No separation of concerns. Difficult to maintain, impossible to test in isolation, and every change redeploys everything. Target architecture: separate app.css, app.js, data.js files.

CRIT-02: ✅ RESOLVED (Mar 2026) — renderAll() Called on Every State Change
Fixed with targeted renders using dirty flags. Added updateTopStatsOnly() and updateProfileOnly() functions.

CRIT-03: ✅ RESOLVED (Mar 2026) — Sequential Supabase Sync Loop
Fixed with batch upsert calls for offer_status and pending_payouts.

2.2 Medium Issues

CRIT-04: Offer data hardcoded in HTML — adding/editing requires a GitHub deploy

CRIT-05: inferCategory() uses regex on badge text — fragile, breaks if badge wording changes

CRIT-06: offerEnrichment is a separate object — should be merged into each offer object

CRIT-07: ✅ RESOLVED (Mar 2026) — formatMoney() rounds to 0 decimal places — now uses .toFixed(2)

CRIT-08: ✅ RESOLVED (Mar 2026) — Password reset flow added. Forgot password link, reset email via Supabase, new password form on redirect.

CRIT-09: Leaderboard shows static fake data, not real Supabase data

CRIT-10: ✅ RESOLVED (Mar 2026) — SW updated to v2. Network-first for HTML pages, cache-first for static assets. External APIs never cached.

2.3 Minor Issues

CRIT-11: No swipe-down gesture to close offer panel (only small X button)

CRIT-12: iOS keyboard pushes form content off screen in auth modal

CRIT-13: No skeleton loaders — offers grid shows empty then pops in

CRIT-14: ✅ RESOLVED (Mar 2026) — BOT_TOKEN moved to Railway Variables, old token revoked via BotFather

CRIT-15: Google Fonts loaded without font-display:swap — blocks rendering

