5.2 Test Cases — Run Before Every Deploy

Auth Tests

TC-A1: New user can sign up with email + password + username → redirected to app → progress row created in Supabase
TC-A2: Existing user can log in → progress loaded from Supabase → XP matches database
TC-A3: Wrong password shows clear error message, does not crash
TC-A4: "Continue without account" skips modal, app works in localStorage-only mode
TC-A5: Password reset email is received within 60 seconds (once implemented)

Progress Sync Tests

TC-S1: Claiming daily XP → state.xp increases → Supabase progress.xp matches after 5 seconds
TC-S2: Marking offer as completed → offer_status row upserted in Supabase
TC-S3: Log saving £100 on Chase → earningsMap updated → Supabase saved_amount updated
TC-S4: Log in on a second device → XP, offer status, and pending payouts all match first device
TC-S5: Supabase unavailable → app continues working from localStorage → no crash

Offer Panel Tests

TC-O1: Tapping any offer card opens slide panel with name, reward, badge, desc
TC-O2: Offer with code shows copy button → tapping copies to clipboard → toast appears
TC-O3: Ticking all steps marks offer as completed automatically
TC-O4: Status buttons (Not started / Pending / Done) update correctly
TC-O5: "Open Offer" button opens URL in new tab
TC-O6: Panel closes on X button tap and on swipe down

API Tests

# Health check
curl https://referral-hunter-bot-production.up.railway.app/health
# Expected: {"status":"ok","bot":"Money Hunters UK"}

# Subscribe endpoint
curl -X POST https://referral-hunter-bot-production.up.railway